AGENT AxiomLanguage
VERSION 1.3
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Define the Axiom Language System in its own terms
GOAL Self-contained language reference expressed entirely in Axiom constructs
     No external programming language syntax permitted
     This spec is the canonical reference for what constitutes valid Axiom
     Parser behavior must match these definitions exactly

CANNOT_MUTATE construct_definitions, semantic_types, validation_rules, strict_mode, block_types

CONSTRAINT Every construct definition must use only Axiom-native syntax
CONSTRAINT No Python, JavaScript, or procedural code references permitted
CONSTRAINT All behavior is expressed declaratively through Axiom constructs
CONSTRAINT This spec is self-describing — it uses only the constructs it defines
CONSTRAINT Construct names are uppercase keywords appearing at the start of a line
CONSTRAINT Section headers are single uppercase words on their own line followed by bullet items
CONSTRAINT Continuation lines are indented lines that extend the previous construct value

RULES
- AGENT names the agent — one per file, required, appears on the first line
- VERSION declares the semantic version — format is major dot minor or major dot minor dot patch
- TRUST_LEVEL declares the trust tier as an integer — delegation flows downward only, never upward
- SANDBOX_AGENT names the sandbox delegate agent for isolated execution
- PURPOSE is a one-line mission statement describing what the agent does
- GOAL is the multi-line objective — continuation lines are indented below the first line
- RECEIVES declares the input contract as name colon type pairs
- EMITS declares the output contract as name colon type pairs
- MUTATES lists the fields this agent may modify at runtime
- CANNOT_MUTATE lists the fields permanently locked — the parser enforces immutability on these
- CONSTRAINT declares a single-line invariant — one invariant per CONSTRAINT keyword, never bundled
- RULES is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet is an operational command the agent follows
- PROCESS is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet is an ordered step executed sequentially
- CHECK is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet is a quality gate evaluated after PROCESS
- FAILURE is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet describes behavior when CHECK gates fail
- OUTPUT is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet describes the format and structure of the response
- SUCCESS is a section header followed by field colon weight pairs — weights must sum to one point zero
- CONCEPT is a named sub-specification block containing its own PURPOSE, APPLIES WHEN, NOT WHEN, PRIORITY, REQUIRES, and EFFECT fields
- WHEN is a section header followed by decision table entries — each entry maps a keyword condition to a concept activation
- SECURITY is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet is a hard security rule that overrides RULES
- TOOLS is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet declares an available tool with permissions and sandbox flags
- DELEGATES is a section header followed by routing entries — each entry maps Agent to Target on a named trigger
- HUMAN_REVIEW is a section header followed by bullet items — each bullet declares a condition requiring human approval
- HISTORY is a section header followed by timestamped change log entries
- Any unrecognized uppercase word on its own line becomes a generic section header collecting bullet items below it
- Blank lines separate logical sections but carry no semantic meaning
- Lines beginning with a dash and space are bullet items belonging to the current section
- Lines beginning with indentation are continuation lines extending the previous value

PROCESS
- Read the file line by line from top to bottom
- Identify construct keywords appearing at the start of each line
- For single-line constructs, capture the value after the keyword and space
- For continuation lines, append the trimmed content to the previous construct value
- For section headers, set the current section and collect subsequent bullet items
- For CONCEPT blocks, enter sub-parsing mode and collect nested fields until the next top-level construct
- For CANNOT_MUTATE fields, register each listed field as immutable for the lifetime of the agent
- After parsing completes, validate the parsed structure against all rules
- Build a system prompt from the parsed structure for injection into the reasoning model
- Sign the resulting manifest with a cryptographic hash for tamper detection

CHECK
- AGENT field is present and non-empty
- VERSION field is present and follows the major dot minor format
- SUCCESS weights sum to exactly one point zero when present
- CANNOT_MUTATE fields are never modified by any save operation
- MUTATES and CANNOT_MUTATE have no overlapping fields
- CONCEPT blocks contain at minimum a PURPOSE field
- WHEN entries reference concepts that exist in the same file or a loaded dependency
- TRUST_LEVEL is an integer between one and five when present
- No purity violations detected — StrictMode rules apply
- DELEGATES routing flows downward in trust level, never upward
- TOOLS entries include permission declarations
- SECURITY rules do not contradict CANNOT_MUTATE fields

FAILURE
- Missing AGENT: file is rejected — status invalid
- Missing VERSION: file is rejected — status invalid
- Purity violation detected: file is rejected with violation description
- SUCCESS weights do not sum to one point zero: file is rejected
- MUTATES and CANNOT_MUTATE overlap: file is rejected — constitutional conflict
- Vague qualifier detected in CONSTRAINT block: warning issued — file status is warning
- WHEN references a nonexistent concept: warning issued
- DELEGATES routes upward in trust: file is rejected — trust hierarchy violation
- CONCEPT missing PURPOSE: warning issued

OUTPUT
- A parsed dictionary keyed by construct name containing all extracted values
- A system prompt string assembled from the parsed structure for model injection
- A validation result with status, issues list, and suggestions
- An HMAC-SHA256 manifest entry for tamper detection on the parsed output

SUCCESS
completeness: 0.3
purity: 0.3
accuracy: 0.2
clarity: 0.2

CONCEPT ConstructSemantics
PURPOSE Classify each construct by its semantic role in the language
APPLIES WHEN validating-block-placement reviewing-spec-structure auditing-language-purity
NOT WHEN reading-content-only generating-system-prompt
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES Each construct belongs to exactly one semantic type
         RULES blocks contain imperative commands
         PROCESS blocks contain procedural steps in execution order
         CHECK blocks contain conditional quality gates
         FAILURE and OUTPUT blocks contain descriptive documentation
         SECURITY blocks contain prohibitive hard rules
         WHEN blocks contain conditional activation mappings
         CONSTRAINT lines contain prohibitive invariants
         CANNOT_MUTATE fields contain constitutional immutable declarations
         CONCEPT blocks are composite sub-specifications
         HISTORY blocks contain declarative change records
         AGENT VERSION TRUST_LEVEL PURPOSE GOAL RECEIVES EMITS SUCCESS TOOLS DELEGATES are declarative metadata
EFFECT Constructs placed in semantically wrong blocks are flagged during validation
       Imperative content in descriptive blocks triggers a warning
       Descriptive content in imperative blocks is permitted but noted
       Constitutional fields override all other semantic types

CONCEPT ValidationPhases
PURPOSE Define the four-phase validation pipeline applied to every Axiom file
APPLIES WHEN file-is-parsed validation-requested pre-save-check
NOT WHEN file-is-being-read-only system-prompt-generation
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES Phase one checks syntax — required fields present, version format valid, SUCCESS weights correct
         Phase two checks purity — no external language patterns in any block
         Phase three checks semantics — no vague qualifiers, no procedural drift in wrong blocks
         Phase four checks history — HISTORY entries have valid structure and timestamps
         All four phases run in order — a phase-one failure skips remaining phases
         Each phase produces its own issue list with severity level
EFFECT Files passing all four phases receive status valid
       Files with warnings but no errors receive status warning
       Files with any error receive status invalid and are rejected

WHEN
- if file is loaded for validation, activate ValidationPhases
- if reviewing construct placement in blocks, activate ConstructSemantics
- if any block contains external language syntax, activate StrictMode
- if CANNOT_MUTATE field modification is attempted, activate ConstitutionalViolation
- if DELEGATES routes upward in trust level, activate TrustHierarchyViolation
- if SUCCESS weights do not sum to one point zero, activate ValidationPhases

HISTORY
- 2026-04-30: v1.3 — Initial self-describing meta-spec created in pure Axiom
